layout.p:
Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 23;
                                                  written lines: 21; Uniform layout. Ruling with hard-point on the hair side of the folio is visible. Daniel and Proverbs begin a new column, and Song of Songs opens a new leaf.The first word of Daniel, Ezra-Nehemiah, Ecclesiaistes and Proverbs, and the first two of Lamentations, Esther and Chronicles are written in larger letters.The centre mark occurs in all the books except in Lamentations, Esther and Chronicles.
